<TITLE> Boat capsize death toll rises to 13 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sunamganj, Jun 8 (bdnews24.com)The death toll from the Sunamganj boat capsize rose to 13 as the rescue workers recovered another body from the Sailchapra Haor. The body was retrieved at around 2pm. Another 13 passengers of the sunken boat were still missing. Local people rescued about 25 to 30 passengers after the boat capsized around 9:30am. Police and locals in the morning retrieved 12 bodies from the water while the rescue efforts were ongoing. The dead could not be immediately identified and the bodies have been sent to the Dharampasha Upazila Health Complex. Dharampasha Upazila Parishad chairman Abdul Awal Talukder said the boat sank while traveling from Balijuri to Badshaganj. Darampasha police chief Majibur Rahman said police and locals were still trying to recover the missing bodies. bdne
